HEADWORD: Glengarry bonnet
<hw>Glen*gar"ry bon"net</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>. <ety>[Name of a
valley in Scotland.]</ety> <def>A kind of Highland Scotch cap for men,
with straight sides and a hollow top sloping to the back, where it is
parted and held together by ribbons or strings.</def></p>

<p><q>The long silk streamers of his <qex>Glengarry bonnet</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>L. Hutton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glenlivet</ent>⟦br⟧
